<h2 id="influenza-1918">Influenza 1918</h2>

<h3 id="what-is-influenza">What is Influenza</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Ancient virus</li>
  <li>Link between birds, pigs and humans</li>
  <li>Classified into types (A, B, C) and by the proteins that coat them (H, N)</li>
  <li>Very contagious (more so than smallpox)</li>
  <li>Seasonal</li>
  <li>Usually low mortality rate</li>
  <li>Increasing number of pandemics since 18th century</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="indian-soldiers-en-route-to-france-1918">Indian Soldiers en Route to France, 1918</h3>

<h3 id="how-did-1918-influenza-kill">How Did 1918 Influenza Kill?</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Quick onset (just 2 hours from healthy to very sick)</li>
  <li>Affected healthy people</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="regulating-influenza">Regulating Influenza</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Mandating procautionary measures</li>
</ul>

<p>Can we compare influenza and COVID-19?</p>

<ul>
  <li>Not really. They are different.</li>
  <li>COVID can’t mutate as quickly</li>
  <li>We also didn’t know that much about Influenza during its pandemic
    <ul>
      <li>We can research COVID easier</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

